2020\n| video2 = [https://www.instagram.com/p/B-JdY3tgi_f/ Police cars on a street of Tiraspol with speakers urging people to remain in home]. 25 March 2020\n| video3 = [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KVVIz5q5UcM Erection of a border between Varni\u021ba (under Moldova administration) and Bender (within Transnistrian control), aiming tension between both sides]. 17 March 2020\n}}\n\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached the internationally unrecognized republic of [[Transnistria]] (officially part of [[Moldova]]) in March 2020.\n\n==Timeline==\n* '''13 March 2020''': The [[Government of Transnistria]] banned all public gatherings.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://novostipmr.com/en/news/20-03-12/quarantine-announcement-preventative-measure|title=Quarantine announcement - preventative measure|newspaper=Novosti Pridnestrovya|date=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n* '''17 March 2020''': The Government of Transnistria announced the shutdown of all kindergartens, schools, colleges and universities until the 5 April.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://novostipmr.com/ru/news/20-03-16/zashchitno-ogranichitelnye-mery-kotorye-budut-deystvovat-v|title=\u0417\u0430\u0449\u0438\u0442\u043d\u043e-\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043c\u0435\u0440\u044b, \u043a\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0440\u044b\u0435 \u0431\u0443\u0434\u0443\u0442 \u0434\u0435\u0439\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0442\u044c \u0432 \u041f\u0440\u0438\u0434\u043d\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435 \u0434\u043e 5 \u0430\u043f\u0440\u0435\u043b\u044f|newspaper=Novosti Pridnestrovya|date=16 March 2020|language=ru}}</ref> The entrance of foreign citizens (including Moldovan ones) to Transnistrian territory was also banned for a period of 19 days.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://novostipmr.com/ru/news/20-03-18/v-ukaz-prezidenta-o-vvedenii-chrezvychaynogo-polozheniya-na|title=\u0412 \u0423\u043a\u0430\u0437 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0437\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430 \"\u041e \u0432\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0438 \u0447\u0440\u0435\u0437\u0432\u044b\u0447\u0430\u0439\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043f\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0435\u0440\u0440\u0438\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0438 \u041f\u0440\u0438\u0434\u043d\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u041c\u043e\u043b\u0434\u0430\u0432\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0420\u0435\u0441\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0438\" \u0432\u043d\u0435\u0441\u0435\u043d\u044b \u0438\u0437\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f|newspaper=Novosti Pridnestrovya|date=18 March 2020|language=ru}}</ref>\n* '''21 March 2020''': The first two positive [[COVID-19]] cases were announced in [[Transnistria]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://agora.md/stiri/68629/au-fost-confirmate-14-cazuri-noi-de-infectie-cu-covid19-bilantul-imbolnavirilor-se-ridica-la-80-de-persoane|title=Au fost confirmate 14 cazuri noi de infec\u021bie cu COVID-19. Bilan\u021bul \u00eemboln\u0103virilor se ridic\u0103 la 80 de persoane|first=Irina|last=Soltan|newspaper=Agora|date=21 March 2020|language=Romanian}}</ref>\n* '''24 March 2020''': The Government of Transnistria announced the suspension of public transport.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://novostipmr.com/ru/news/20-03-23/obshchestvennyy-transport-vremenno-prekrashchaet-svoyu-rabotu|title=\u041e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0441\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442 \u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e \u043f\u0440\u0435\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0449\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u0441\u0432\u043e\u044e \u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0443|newspaper=Novosti Pridnestrovya|date=23 March 2020|language=ru}}</ref>\n* '''25 March 2020''': According to the [[television channel]] [[TV PMR]], the [[Government of Transnistria]] reported that there are 7 people infected with coronavirus, including 2 children.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://telegraph.md/update-cate-persoane-din-stanga-nistrului-sunt-infectate-cu-noul-coronavirus/|title=UPDATE // C\u00e2te persoane din st\u00e2nga Nistrului sunt infectate cu noul coronavirus|newspaper=Telegraph|date=23 March 2020|language=Romanian}}</ref>\n* '''30 March 2020''': By decree of the [[Ministry of Internal Affairs of Transnistria]], during the state of emergency, all citizens must carry an [[identity document]] and a special permission to be outside of their houses.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mvdpmr.org/novosti/glavnaya-tema-koronavirus/30615-opershtab-obyazat-grazhdan-imet-pri-sebe-pasport.html|title=\u041e\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0448\u0442\u0430\u0431: \"\u041e\u0431\u044f\u0437\u0430\u0442\u044c \u0433\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0434\u0430\u043d \u0438\u043c\u0435\u0442\u044c \u043f\u0440\u0438 \u0441\u0435\u0431\u0435 \u043f\u0430\u0441\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\"|newspaper=[[Ministry of Internal Affairs of Transnistria]]|date=30 March 2020|language=ru}}</ref>\n* '''31 March 2020''': A 55-year-old woman from [[Tiraspol]] who suffered of [[heart problems]] and [[diabetes]] is the first deceased by COVID-19 in Transnistria. At the time of her death, she was in an [[intensive care unit]] connected to a [[ventilator]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://novostipmr.com/ru/news/20-03-31/tri-cheloveka-skonchalis-v-slobodzeyskoy-crb|title=\u0422\u0440\u0438 \u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043a\u0430 \u0441\u043a\u043e\u043d\u0447\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0441\u044c \u0432 \u0421\u043b\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0434\u0437\u0435\u0439\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0426\u0420\u0411|newspaper=Novosti Pridnestrovya|date=31 March 2020|language=ru}}</ref>\n\n== Statistics ==\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|linewidth=1\n|showSymbols=1\n|width=850\n|colors=#F46D43,#000000,#C4ADA0,#C4ADB0,#C4ADC0\n|showValues=\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|xAxisAngle=-40\n|x= 21 Mar, 22 Mar, 23 Mar, 24 Mar, 25 Mar, 26 Mar, 27 Mar, 28 Mar, 29 Mar, 30 Mar, 31 Mar, 1 Apr, 2 Apr\n|yAxisTitle=No. of cases\n|legend=Legend\n|y1= 2, 2, 6, 6, 6, 9, 11, 1